model AllOrNothing

-- ===========================================================
-- Synthetic fixture for use2qubo's own test suite.
-- No relation to any example under articles/qmod_2026/examples/ --
-- deliberately generic so editing the paper's examples can never
-- affect this model's meaning.
--
-- Picker has 4 candidate Options; Chosen(Picker,Option) is the sole
-- decision-variable association (nVars=4). The invariant below is
-- true only when ALL 4 are chosen, i.e. its exact multilinear
-- representation is the single pure top-degree monomial
-- x1*x2*x3*x4, with every lower-degree coefficient exactly zero.
-- With max_degree capped at 3 (< n=4) in qubo_config.json, that
-- top-degree term can never be captured: the derived QUBO is
-- guaranteed to remain inexact at the cap, deterministically,
-- regardless of how much sampling escalates.
-- ===========================================================

class Picker
end

class Option
end

association Chosen between
  Picker[1] role picker
  Option[*] role options
end

constraints

context Picker
  inv allChosen:
    self.options->size() = 4
